https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/sites/.Strength: 75 mg solution (1 ml), 150 mg solution (1 ml), 300 mg solution (2 ml)
https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/sites/.Indications: Primary hypercholesterolaemia and mixed dyslipidaemia; established atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease
https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/sites/.Posology: Adults (init: 75 mg every 2 weeks, may increase to 150/300 mg); Paediatric (8+ years: 150/300 mg Q2W or Q4W based on weight); Renal/hepatic impairment: no adjustment needed for mild/moderate
https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/sites/.Special Warnings and Precautions: Traceability, allergic reactions (angioedema, hypersensitivity vasculitis), local injection site reactions, possible accumulation of anti-drug antibodies (ADAs), concurrent use with statins/reduced exposure, monitoring for low LDL-C.
https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/sites/.Shelf Life: 3 years for some presentations (e.g., 75 mg pen), 2 years for others (e.g., 150 mg pen)
https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/sites/.Storage Conditions: Store in refrigerator (2°C to 8°C), protect from light, may be stored below 25°C for up to 30 days post-refrigerator removal, discard after 30 days.
